e domestic super-elite who use the levers of political power to channel foreign capital into real estate and manufacturing projects, conspicuous consumption is a means of projecting an image of Asian ascendancy to potential investors. For Viet Kieus and Westerners who bring remittances into the local economy, personal relationships with local sex workers reinforce their ideas of Asia's rise and Western decline, while simultaneously bolstering their diminished masculinity. Dealing in Desire illuminates Ho Chi Minh City's sex industry as not just a microcosm of the global economy, but a critical space where dreams and deals are traded.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aSex-oriented businessesxVietnamxVietnam. 0aSex-oriented businesseszVietnam. 4aasian businessmen. 4abiography. 4ablack market. 4abudget tourist. 4acounselor. 4adecline of western civilization. 4aethnography. 4aillegal trade. 4ainformal economy. 4amodern slavery. 4apsychologist. 4arise of asia. 4asaigon hostess bars. 4asex trade. 4asex trafficking. 4asex worker. 4asex workers. 4asexual slavery. 4asuper-elite. 4asurvivor. 4atherapist. 4aviet kieus. 4avietnam. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311062111208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520960688423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520960688.jpg  a978-3-11-062111-2  UC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FA